### Display

<%= partial "components/font_sample", :locals => { :font => "display" } %>

**Newslab** is used for headlines and titles, generally in a light weight.

- Foundry: [Latinotype](http://www.latinotype.com/30)
- Vendors: [Fontspring](https://www.fontspring.com/fonts/latinotype/newslab)
- Alternate system fonts: Georgia, Palatino

### Accent

<%= partial "components/font_sample", :locals => { :font => "accent" } %>

**Gibson** is used for subheads, interface elements, and secondary text like sidebars.

- Foundry: [Canada Type](http://canadatype.net/fonts/gibson)
- Vendors: [Fontspring](https://www.fontspring.com/fonts/canada-type/gibson)
- Alternate system fonts: Tahoma, Lucida Grande

### Body

<%= partial "components/font_sample", :locals => { :font => "body", :styles => ["regular", "bold", "italic"] } %>

**Merriweather**, a free font, is used for running text in the main body.

- Foundry: [Sorkin Type](http://sorkintype.com/fonts.html#mw)
- Vendors: [Google Fonts](https://www.google.com/fonts/specimen/Merriweather), [FontSquirrel](https://www.fontsquirrel.com/fonts/merriweather)
- Alternative system fonts: Georgia, Palatino
